==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Light-ship
<hw>Light"-ship`</hw></mhw>
<pr>(l⟦imac⟧t"sh⟦icr⟧p`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Naut.)</fld> <def>A
vessel equipped like a lighthouse, carrying at the masthead a brilliant
light, and moored off a shoal or place of dangerous navigation where a
permanent lighthouse would be impracticable, to serve as a guide for
mariners; <as>as, the Ambrose <ex>lightship</ex> off New York was rammed
and damaged in 1950 by the Santa Monica</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> + <source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>light-skinned</ent>⟦br⟧
